## System Architecture & Data Flow

SnapSummary is structured as a decoupled web application containing a **React SPA (Single Page Application)** frontend and a **Django REST Framework (DRF)** backend API. It leverages **Groq cloud services** for fast, hardware-accelerated AI models (Llama 3.3 and Whisper Large V3) and uses **FFmpeg** on the host operating system for media file preparation.

### System Architecture Diagram

```mermaid
graph TD
    User([User Client]) <-->|React UI / axios| FE[React Frontend SPA]
    FE <-->|REST API / JSON / Multipart| BE[Django REST Framework Backend]
    BE <-->|Read/Write| DB[(SQLite Database)]
    BE -->|1. Create Async Thread| TH[Background Thread]
    TH -->|FFmpeg Command Line| FF[Host OS FFmpeg]
    TH -->|pdfplumber / txt read| PDF[Text Extractor]
    TH <-->|HTTPS REST API| Groq[Groq API Services]
    Groq <-->|Transcription| Whisper[Whisper Large V3]
    Groq <-->|Summarization & QA Chat| LLaMA[LLaMA 3.3 70B Versatile]
```

### Main Operations Loop

1. **Upload & Ingestion**: The React frontend validates the chosen file and transmits it via `FormData` to `/api/upload/`.
2. **Persistence**: The backend database records a new summary row with status `processing`.
3. **Threading**: The server starts a new Python background thread (non-daemon) to handle processing without blocking the API response, returning `201 Created` with the ID to the client immediately.
4. **Extraction & AI**: The thread extracts text from documents or converts media into an MP3 file (using shell calls to `ffmpeg`) and sends it to the Groq APIs. The resulting text transcript is passed to Groq LLaMA 3.3 to create a structured summary.
5. **Polling**: The React frontend polls `/api/summaries/{id}/` every 3 seconds. Once the background processing finishes, status shifts to `done` or `error`, updating the UI state.
6. **Chat (RAG)**: Users engage in a factual QA session with Aira (chatbot) based exclusively on the extracted text, sending inquiries to `/api/summaries/{id}/chat/`.

