## Database Schema

The database relies on a single-table design (`summaries`) to keep transactions and reads extremely fast.

### `Summary` Model Configuration

* **DB Table Name**: `summaries`
* **Default Order**: `-created_at` (latest items display first)

| Column Name | Database Data Type | Description / Notes | Constraints |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `id` | `BigAutoField` (Integer) | Primary key, automatically incremented | Primary Key, Unique |
| `original_filename` | `varchar(255)` | Preserves the name of the file uploaded by the user | Required |
| `file` | `varchar(100)` | Relative path to the uploaded file in media directories | `upload_to='uploads/'` |
| `file_size` | `bigint` | File size stored in bytes | Required |
| `file_type` | `varchar(20)` | Categories: `document`, `audio`, or `video` | Required |
| `status` | `varchar(20)` | Tracks current processing cycle: `processing`, `done`, or `error` | Default: `'processing'` |
| `error_message` | `text` | Trace or custom error message if status is set to `error` | Nullable, Blankable |
| `transcript` | `text` | Raw text extracted from document or transcribed by Whisper | Nullable, Blankable |
| `summary` | `text` | Structurally generated markdown summary from Groq LLaMA | Nullable, Blankable |
| `language` | `varchar(50)` | Identified language (e.g. `'en'` from audio, or `'text'` for files) | Nullable, Blankable |
| `duration_seconds` | `double precision` | Running length of audio or video files | Nullable, Blankable |
| `created_at` | `datetime` | Creation timestamp | `auto_now_add=True` |
| `updated_at` | `datetime` | Latest timestamp change | `auto_now=True` |

### Django Model Computed Properties
* **`file_size_mb`**: Divides the database `file_size` (bytes) by `1,048,576` ($1024^2$) and rounds the outcome to 2 decimal places to output size in megabytes.

