## Future Roadmap & Architecture Enhancements

To upgrade SnapSummary from a hobby/learning project to a production-ready application:

### Short-Term Priorities (1-2 Months)
* **Fix Command Injection**: Replace `os.system` call with `subprocess.run` as detailed in the security section.
* **Fix DB Settings**: Bind the database configuration to read environment variables (like `DATABASE_URL`) so it can connect to PostgreSQL in both docker-compose and production environments.
* **Add JWT Authentication**: Set up Django REST Framework SimpleJWT or similar token authentication so users can register, log in, and view only their own uploaded summaries.

### Medium-Term Priorities (3-6 Months)
* **Integrate Celery & Redis**: Offload file processing from Python threads to Celery workers to prevent data loss when web servers cycle.
* **Implement Document Chunking**: Divide long text transcripts into chunks (e.g. 2,000 words each), summarize them individually, and compile the summaries together to bypass context window limits.
* **Integrate Vector Database**: Embed chunked text snippets using a lightweight model and save them to a local vector store (e.g., ChromaDB, PgVector) or external cloud service (e.g., Pinecone) to enable semantic retrieval for Aira chat.

### Long-Term Priorities (6-12 Months)
* **Streaming Responses**: Enable Server-Sent Events (SSE) to stream answers from Groq LLaMA word-by-word into the React UI chat panel.
* **Webhooks / Event Notifications**: Replace the 3-second client polling mechanism with WebSockets to update file states dynamically.
* **CDN File Storage**: Store uploaded files in Amazon S3 or Google Cloud Storage instead of the local server disk.
